WEBVTT

00:13.213 --> 00:14.213
Terrific!

00:34.630 --> 00:37.338
So I put my finger here,
and check this...

00:37.713 --> 00:40.088
the watch tells me I have a heart problem.

00:40.171 --> 00:42.088
Wouldn't a mirror tell you the same thing?

00:42.171 --> 00:44.213
Yeah, but this has weather, too.

00:44.296 --> 00:45.130
Okay.

00:45.505 --> 00:47.838
We got an hour until
we're meeting the ladies for dinner.

00:47.921 --> 00:49.130
- Yeah.
- You wanna catch a beer?

00:49.213 --> 00:51.088
I can't. I gotta run a few errands.

00:51.171 --> 00:53.588
What? You don't want a beer? What's wrong?

00:53.671 --> 00:54.630
I...

00:54.963 --> 00:57.671
got the results back
from the detective exam.

00:57.755 --> 01:00.755
You failed again?
This is why I never took that test.

01:00.838 --> 01:02.963
All the anxiety and disappointment.

01:03.046 --> 01:05.755
At some point, you have to realize
you have hit your ceiling

01:05.838 --> 01:07.005
and just give up.

01:07.088 --> 01:09.088
You know, you should go around
and speak at schools.

01:09.171 --> 01:11.963
- That was very inspiring.
- I should. Kids need to hear this shit.

01:12.046 --> 01:13.046
I don't get it, man.

01:13.130 --> 01:15.963
I know all the answers,
I just freeze under pressure.

01:16.046 --> 01:18.505
You know, I can't take the exam
for, like, three more months,

01:18.588 --> 01:20.213
so I gotta continue lying to Audrey.

01:20.296 --> 01:22.005
So when we're at dinner tonight, please,

01:22.088 --> 01:23.463
- tell your wi--
- Ah! No.

01:23.546 --> 01:25.921
Come on, man.
You know I'll lie for you anytime.

01:26.005 --> 01:28.046
I will cover up dead bodies for you.

01:28.130 --> 01:32.255
But if I ask Holly to lie to your wife,
there's no way we're messing around.

01:32.338 --> 01:33.421
It's Freaky Friday!

01:33.505 --> 01:36.463
You don't have to lie,
just tell her to ignore when I'm lying.

01:36.546 --> 01:37.546
That's it.

01:38.380 --> 01:39.630
- Okay, fine.
- Thank you.

01:39.713 --> 01:41.088
You owe me.

01:41.171 --> 01:42.005
See you tonight.

01:45.296 --> 01:47.421
I gotta get Claritin. Claritin.

01:47.505 --> 01:49.213
Oh, my God! Look!

01:49.921 --> 01:51.505
He took her in a helicopter?

01:51.796 --> 01:53.880
My husband won't even pay for Uber Black.

01:53.963 --> 01:57.505
Yeah. I don't even--
I can't even remember the last time

01:57.588 --> 02:01.213
that Nick did anything
even remotely romantic.

02:01.463 --> 02:04.505
I mean, he used to leave me,
like, cute little mixtapes,

02:04.755 --> 02:06.671
little love notes in the bathroom.

02:06.755 --> 02:07.963
Love notes are dead.

02:08.045 --> 02:09.380
When my husband wants to have sex,

02:09.463 --> 02:11.338
he just texts me the eggplant
and doughnut emoji.

02:11.671 --> 02:13.171
Eggplant and doughnut--

02:14.088 --> 02:15.588
Oh. He's the eggplant.

02:15.880 --> 02:17.838
More like a fingerling potato.

02:17.921 --> 02:19.255
It doesn't take that much.

02:19.338 --> 02:21.713
There are guys at the intersection
selling flowers.

02:21.796 --> 02:24.255
You just roll down the window,
grab a bunch, bring 'em home.

02:24.338 --> 02:27.171
- I mean, they couldn't make it any easier.
- No kidding.

02:27.255 --> 02:29.630
I mean, tomorrow
is our 15th wedding anniversary.

02:30.171 --> 02:33.338
I'm still waiting on that trip to Europe
he promised me on our wedding day.

02:33.421 --> 02:35.255
- That's been 15 years?
- Yeah.

02:35.338 --> 02:37.296
I could have walked to Europe by now.

02:37.380 --> 02:38.921
You know, you just have to tell him.

02:39.005 --> 02:42.796
I just don't want to have to tell him.
I just want him to know.

02:42.880 --> 02:44.588
- No, they never just know.
- I know.

02:44.671 --> 02:46.755
- That doesn't happen.
- You have to tell men everything.

02:46.838 --> 02:49.171
If you want the dishes to not go
in the sink, you have to tell them.

02:49.255 --> 02:51.171
If you want him to shower
before he comes to bed,

02:51.255 --> 02:52.505
- you have to ask him.
- Ugh.

02:52.588 --> 02:54.963
That's why they have those signs
in bathrooms at restaurants

02:55.046 --> 02:57.046
to tell employees to wash their hands.

02:57.130 --> 02:59.296
Those aren't for women, guys.
Those are for men.

02:59.380 --> 03:02.380
Or maybe you could just text him,
airplane, wine glass,

03:02.463 --> 03:05.380
Italian flag, eggplant,
doughnut, doughnut, doughnut.

03:24.921 --> 03:26.005
Let's go with the 50.

03:31.213 --> 03:32.296
Claritin...

03:40.213 --> 03:41.088
Hi, welcome.

03:41.796 --> 03:42.713
Thank you.

03:42.838 --> 03:44.421
Thanks a lot.

03:44.505 --> 03:47.046
Are you gonna tell 'em
about the stuff in your backpack?

03:47.380 --> 03:49.296
Mind your own business, man.
I'm paying for this.

03:49.838 --> 03:51.713
I like your sneakers.
They must be expensive.

03:51.796 --> 03:53.963
Is that why can't afford
the Monster Energy Drink

03:54.046 --> 03:55.546
or the Flamin' Hot Cheetos?

03:56.796 --> 03:59.046
- Hang on. Hang on.
- Hey, let go of me, man.

04:01.088 --> 04:02.421
I can't believe I was right.

04:03.088 --> 04:05.463
Keep your mouth shut.
I'll mess you up, old man.

04:05.546 --> 04:07.005
Old man. Oh, my God.

04:07.088 --> 04:08.171
First of all,

04:08.630 --> 04:11.630
I should throw you in jail
just for calling me "old man,"

04:11.713 --> 04:13.713
but you bring that stuff back,

04:13.796 --> 04:17.005
I'll let you go 'cause I'm late
for dinner and I'm hungry as shit.

04:17.296 --> 04:18.171
Go ahead.

04:21.130 --> 04:23.296
- Tylenol PM? Am I right?
- No.

04:23.380 --> 04:26.171
It's not good for that.
It depends on what time of year you go.

04:26.255 --> 04:28.005
That makes sense.
Can I get another?

04:28.296 --> 04:29.755
We're gonna have another one?

04:29.838 --> 04:33.463
I'm just saying, we're paying today.
Maybe you can take it easy a little bit.

04:33.546 --> 04:36.046
Hey, hey. Nick. Nick.
What-- What's wrong with you?

04:36.130 --> 04:38.796
Sorry. Should I not order
another drink, Detective?

04:39.421 --> 04:40.755
No. Holly, order another drink.

04:40.838 --> 04:43.130
Order as much as you want.
I was joking around.

04:43.213 --> 04:44.421
- That's not funny.
- The reason--

04:44.505 --> 04:47.255
I'm just in a great mood
because I had a great day today.

04:47.338 --> 04:50.130
- Did we have a great day or what?
- It was a fabulous day. Incredible day.

04:50.213 --> 04:52.380
Really? Did you get another hot case?

04:52.755 --> 04:53.588
Of what?

04:53.671 --> 04:55.296
"What."

04:55.380 --> 04:56.796
That was good. No, listen.

04:56.880 --> 04:58.463
Going great, kid. I promise you.

04:58.546 --> 05:00.921
It's like, uh, they're trusting me
more and more,

05:01.005 --> 05:03.213
and I, um, I wish I could tell you
what it was,

05:03.296 --> 05:04.546
but it's-- it's confidential.

05:04.630 --> 05:06.421
- Wait a second.
- What?

05:06.505 --> 05:07.630
Oh, my God.

05:07.713 --> 05:09.588
- What is this?
- What is that?

05:09.671 --> 05:12.421
My baby Jimmy got it for me
for my birthday.

05:12.505 --> 05:13.338
- Jimmy!
- What?

05:13.421 --> 05:16.130
- Celebration diamonds.
- Oh, my gosh.

05:16.213 --> 05:17.838
- It's gorgeous!
- Thank you, Audrey.

05:17.921 --> 05:19.380
- Very expensive.
- Wow, Jimmy.

05:19.921 --> 05:22.880
I got you something special.
I promise, you're gonna be very happy.

05:22.963 --> 05:24.255
- Really?
- I can't wait.

05:24.338 --> 05:27.671
See, I would've pegged you, Nick,
as an Amazon gift card kinda guy,

05:27.755 --> 05:29.630
but... I'm no detective.

05:30.963 --> 05:32.755
Hey! You know what, guys?

05:32.838 --> 05:36.546
Let's toast to my friends,
Nick and Audrey.

05:36.630 --> 05:37.963
Fifteen wonderful years.

05:38.046 --> 05:39.046
Absolutely.

05:39.130 --> 05:41.338
- Fifteen.
- Here's to true love, guys.

05:41.421 --> 05:42.255
Fifteen.

05:42.338 --> 05:43.171
- True love.
- Yeah.

05:50.005 --> 05:53.630
Dinner was insane, but that's expected.

05:55.088 --> 05:56.171
But I'll tell you what,

05:56.255 --> 05:58.880
I want to record Holly
chewing her ice cubes,

05:58.963 --> 06:01.421
use it as my alarm in the morning.
That's--

06:01.505 --> 06:03.921
Guarantee me of wanting to
wake up and leave.

06:08.588 --> 06:10.796
What's the matter?
You didn't like that joke?

06:13.171 --> 06:14.338
I'm flossing.

06:14.421 --> 06:15.713
I can see that.

06:16.671 --> 06:18.421
You're doing it extra hard tonight.

06:19.463 --> 06:22.046
And I'm not sleeping with
the fan on tonight. I hate that sound.

06:22.463 --> 06:24.963
No fan necessary.
We'll crank the AC, babe.

06:29.463 --> 06:30.880
Uh-oh. What, what, what?

06:30.963 --> 06:32.838
You're gonna yell at me?
I can see this. Hang on.

06:32.921 --> 06:34.713
Why don't you do some more angry flossing?

06:35.546 --> 06:37.880
How come we haven't gone to Europe, Nick?

06:38.796 --> 06:40.130
You have to explain this to me.

06:40.921 --> 06:42.005
We never go anywhere.

06:42.088 --> 06:44.921
We travel.
I took you to the Poconos that time.

06:45.005 --> 06:46.255
What? The Poco-- That was--

06:46.338 --> 06:47.755
That was for a funeral, Nick.

06:48.171 --> 06:50.630
How about, uh, when we went to Virginia

06:50.713 --> 06:52.963
when my uncle was in a hospice
and we got to see him die?

06:53.046 --> 06:54.630
- We did that.
- Ugh, Nick. Come on.

06:54.713 --> 06:56.171
I'm talking about the postcard.

06:56.255 --> 06:59.338
- You don't remember that?
- I remember it. Of course I remember it.

06:59.838 --> 07:02.921
It's been 15 years, Nick.
I don't know what we're waitin' for.

07:05.963 --> 07:08.546
Now you've gone and done it, Audrey.

07:08.630 --> 07:10.296
What? What'd I do?

07:12.005 --> 07:14.005
I told you I had something big
for you at dinner,

07:14.088 --> 07:16.255
and you couldn't wait till
tomorrow morning?

07:17.588 --> 07:18.463
No.

07:19.796 --> 07:22.005
We're finally going to Europe.
Happy anniversary.

07:22.588 --> 07:25.088
Oh, my God. I have chills.

07:25.171 --> 07:28.005
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

07:28.088 --> 07:30.130
Oh, my God! I'm so--

07:30.630 --> 07:33.130
- I ruined your surprise!
- Shh. You didn't ruin anything.

07:33.213 --> 07:35.255
You're the greatest. You deserve it.
I love you.

07:35.338 --> 07:37.880
- I love you!
- It's still a surprise. I swear.

07:42.046 --> 07:44.921
- We can afford it, right? This is all--
- We can afford it, of course.

07:45.005 --> 07:46.505
- Okay.
- I'm getting my raise this year.

07:46.588 --> 07:48.255
- Right.
- We're all set. Come on.

07:48.671 --> 07:50.046
- Hello. Hi.
- Hello.

07:50.130 --> 07:51.921
So, uh, we are on our honeymoon,

07:52.005 --> 07:54.546
and I was wondering
if we could possibly get an upgrade

07:54.630 --> 07:57.005
because I have miles. Maybe--

07:57.088 --> 08:00.380
I don't even know if it's from
this airline, but do they expire, or--

08:00.463 --> 08:02.630
Sir, you would have needed
to request that in advance.

08:02.713 --> 08:04.296
- Yeah.
- Right this way, please.

08:04.380 --> 08:06.963
- Thank you. I'm so sorry.
- We did try advance. I tried calling.

08:07.046 --> 08:08.921
- And, um, nobody--
- Who'd you call?

08:09.005 --> 08:10.546
- Crazy busy signals.
- Really?

08:10.630 --> 08:12.505
- It's the busy signals!
- Who did you try to call?

08:16.838 --> 08:19.005
I don't want to give it away.
It was the butler.

08:19.088 --> 08:20.463
The butler did it.

08:21.255 --> 08:22.921
It's never the butler who did it.

08:23.880 --> 08:25.671
I don't even think there are butlers.

08:25.755 --> 08:28.921
That's just a word created
for those goofy books you're addicted to.

08:29.005 --> 08:30.963
Would you just please, please shh?

08:31.046 --> 08:34.087
Leave my books alone, okay?
Just let me read.

08:34.171 --> 08:36.212
I just like-- Makes me happy.

08:36.296 --> 08:38.171
Are you okay? You're cranky.
Are you bored?

08:38.255 --> 08:40.046
- I'm gonna go to sleep.
- Take a nap.

08:40.587 --> 08:42.212
- Are you okay with that?
- Wait, don't--

08:42.296 --> 08:44.963
But just, please, don't--
don't lay all the way back.

08:45.546 --> 08:46.963
- Don't take it back?
- No.

08:47.046 --> 08:48.796
Why? You don't want
my double chin to show?

08:48.880 --> 08:51.546
It's not your chins, okay. It's just rude.

08:51.630 --> 08:52.505
Yes.

08:52.588 --> 08:54.213
- Okay. 'Cause you splay out.
- All right.

08:54.296 --> 08:57.421
And then your seat is in, like,
the lap of the guy behind you.

08:57.505 --> 09:00.421
- So just be considerate of everybody.
- I'll stay up. Thank you.

09:01.255 --> 09:02.296
Timber.

09:11.005 --> 09:12.463
Oh, excuse me.

09:12.546 --> 09:13.963
- Hi.
- Hello. Hi.

09:14.046 --> 09:16.546
Could I please have some earplugs?

09:16.630 --> 09:17.588
Yes.

09:17.671 --> 09:18.880
For nine dollars.

09:19.338 --> 09:21.755
Nine dollars? For earplugs?

09:21.838 --> 09:22.755
Yes.

09:23.046 --> 09:24.838
That's okay. I'll just--

09:25.380 --> 09:26.630
I'll just use my peanuts.

09:28.380 --> 09:29.338
I'll just--

09:54.088 --> 09:54.921
Wow.

10:11.296 --> 10:12.380
Oh...

10:13.880 --> 10:14.880
Mm.

10:21.963 --> 10:23.796
A fellow insomniac, I see.

10:23.880 --> 10:24.880
Jesus.

10:24.963 --> 10:26.213
Yes. I--

10:26.796 --> 10:28.588
Yep. I know, right?

10:28.671 --> 10:30.796
I just cannot sleep on these things.

10:31.046 --> 10:32.671
So what brings you across the pond?

10:32.755 --> 10:35.713
Actually, it's my-- it's my honeymoon.

10:35.796 --> 10:37.296
Oh. Congratulations.

10:37.380 --> 10:39.171
- Thank you.
- Where's your husband?

10:39.755 --> 10:40.630
Dead.

10:41.171 --> 10:43.713
Asleep. He's dead-- dead asleep.

10:43.796 --> 10:45.838
We've actually been married for 15 years,

10:45.921 --> 10:49.338
but we just have been very, very,
very, very busy.

10:49.588 --> 10:52.838
Then a toast to the whirlwind
that is your life.

10:54.046 --> 10:55.088
Yes.

10:55.171 --> 10:56.338
- Sorry, ma'am.
- Oh, yes!

10:56.421 --> 10:58.380
The bar is for
first class passengers only.

10:58.463 --> 11:00.880
Of course. Of course it is.
I'm so sorry, yes.

11:00.963 --> 11:04.130
I will head back to the lower class cabin

11:04.213 --> 11:06.421
and sit where I should and, uh...

11:06.963 --> 11:07.921
shovel some coal.

11:08.005 --> 11:09.130
She's my guest.

11:09.213 --> 11:11.880
Unfortunately, sir,
she'd need her own first class ticket.

11:11.963 --> 11:13.296
Charles Cavendish.

11:14.463 --> 11:15.671
I'm so sorry, sir.

11:19.588 --> 11:20.588
Whoa!

11:21.505 --> 11:22.963
Charles Cavendish?

11:23.505 --> 11:24.421
Is that your real name?

11:24.505 --> 11:26.005
I'm afraid so.

11:26.088 --> 11:28.671
I mean, that sounds like
it just fell right out of a...

11:28.755 --> 11:29.921
mystery novel.

11:30.630 --> 11:32.463
And which character would I be?

11:33.546 --> 11:35.880
Name like that,
you'd have to be the bad guy.

11:37.546 --> 11:38.380
Well...

11:39.213 --> 11:40.421
here's to the bad guys.

11:56.838 --> 11:59.088
- Okay, so your fiancée...
- Hm.

11:59.796 --> 12:00.796
...leaves you...

12:01.796 --> 12:05.130
...for your elderly uncle--

12:05.213 --> 12:07.755
Will you two kindly shut up?

12:07.838 --> 12:09.005
Oh, be quiet.

12:09.505 --> 12:12.588
Or we shall tell everyone about the ferret
you've smuggled in here.

12:14.046 --> 12:16.921
The whole thing is tawdry, I know.

12:17.005 --> 12:18.921
- Tawdry.
- He desired my betrothed,

12:19.005 --> 12:21.671
and Uncle Malcolm always gets
what he wants.

12:21.755 --> 12:23.713
Malcolm. Uncle Malcolm.

12:24.296 --> 12:25.338
- Quince.
- Uncle--

12:26.130 --> 12:29.463
Malcolm Quince is your uncle?
That billionaire?

12:29.796 --> 12:31.796
- That's the one.
- Oh, my gosh.

12:32.546 --> 12:34.963
He looks just like this...

12:35.755 --> 12:39.296
if this wrinkled olive had $70 billion.

12:40.213 --> 12:41.546
Seventy billion dollars.

12:41.630 --> 12:44.213
I'm traveling to Monaco with the newlyweds
on his yacht

12:44.296 --> 12:45.838
for the Grand Prix this weekend.

12:46.171 --> 12:48.005
Why? Why would you do that?

12:48.088 --> 12:50.296
Why would you go on their yacht
after what they just did?

12:50.380 --> 12:52.296
Because I'm English, Mrs. Spitz.

12:52.963 --> 12:55.171
- I'm a glutton for social masochism.
- Oh.

12:55.255 --> 12:59.880
And I plan on getting blind drunk
and ruining the festivities.

13:01.171 --> 13:03.046
Okay. I support that.

13:03.380 --> 13:05.213
- I say, Audrey...
- Hm.

13:06.255 --> 13:08.880
Do you and your husband
have plans this weekend?

13:13.713 --> 13:16.171
You made a joke. That's--

13:17.796 --> 13:20.838
Holy shit! This plane has a bar?

13:20.921 --> 13:22.963
Sir, this is the first class lounge.

13:23.046 --> 13:25.005
I'm gonna have to ask you
to return to your seat.

13:25.088 --> 13:26.421
There's bars on planes now?

13:26.505 --> 13:28.421
Planes have bars now. In first class.

13:28.505 --> 13:31.505
This is-- Man, I wish my mother was
still alive to see this.

13:31.588 --> 13:33.171
She was an alcoholic, but a nice one.

13:33.255 --> 13:35.713
Sir, if you don't return to your seat,
I'm gonna have to call--

13:35.796 --> 13:36.671
The cops.

13:37.255 --> 13:38.213
So that's my wife

13:38.296 --> 13:41.838
talking to that handsome guy over there
with the one chin.

13:42.171 --> 13:46.046
So I'm gonna go break that shit up,
possibly grab myself a beer,

13:46.130 --> 13:47.421
maybe you a Xanax.

13:49.505 --> 13:51.796
...the wine on board is worth a letter.

13:52.630 --> 13:54.796
People don't write letters
anymore, do they?

13:55.338 --> 13:58.421
- Such a pity.
- It's just, it's all so tactical.

13:58.963 --> 14:00.338
Yeah, that's true.

14:01.796 --> 14:02.671
Hey!

14:02.755 --> 14:03.588
Nick.

14:03.671 --> 14:06.380
- How are you?
- Hi, honey. You're awake.

14:06.838 --> 14:08.171
- Was your nappie good?
- Been awake.

14:08.255 --> 14:09.838
- I was looking for you.
- I know, I'm--

14:09.921 --> 14:12.296
- Well, I met this lovely gentleman.
- Oh, yeah?

14:12.380 --> 14:14.755
I'd like you to meet Charles Cavendish.

14:14.838 --> 14:16.421
- He's a lord. Right?
- How do you do?

14:16.505 --> 14:18.588
- A lord?
- Well, actually a viscount.

14:18.671 --> 14:21.088
- Oh.
- Although viscounts are addressed as Lord,

14:21.171 --> 14:23.713
which probably accounts
for the lovely Audrey's confusion.

14:23.796 --> 14:25.921
There you go.
She gets confused with me too.

14:26.005 --> 14:28.546
Sometimes I'm the king.
Sometimes I'm Daddy.

14:29.130 --> 14:31.546
So... can I get a Labatts, brother?

14:32.505 --> 14:33.796
That'll be 17 euro.

14:33.880 --> 14:35.130
No, no, no. Please.

14:35.213 --> 14:36.380
The beer is on me.

14:36.463 --> 14:39.171
I'm not just taking a beer
from somebody I don't know.

14:39.255 --> 14:40.255
Oh, my gosh.

14:40.338 --> 14:44.338
And I do hope you take advantage
of my other offer.

14:44.421 --> 14:46.421
Hey. I'm not just gonna stand here

14:46.505 --> 14:49.130
while you offer to pay me
to have sex with my wife.

14:49.213 --> 14:51.213
But out of curiosity,
how much are we talking?

14:51.296 --> 14:52.463
- Great.
