27:47.005 --> 27:49.421
A gift to the family from Marco Polo,

27:49.755 --> 27:50.963
or so the legend says.

27:51.046 --> 27:51.921
God.

27:52.296 --> 27:54.796
Nick's grandmother gave us
a toaster from Sears.

27:54.880 --> 27:56.880
So the legend says.

28:08.338 --> 28:09.963
Oh, look.

28:10.046 --> 28:12.046
Here comes Daddy.

28:13.838 --> 28:14.838
What's that?

28:26.338 --> 28:27.588
Captain Wong,

28:28.046 --> 28:30.546
I'd like to address my guests privately.

28:30.796 --> 28:31.755
Certainly.

28:41.005 --> 28:41.880
My friends,

28:42.713 --> 28:45.380
welcome to the <i>Mediterranean Queen.</i>

28:45.463 --> 28:48.130
I can't tell you
how much it warms my heart

28:48.755 --> 28:50.963
that you have made this trip here

28:51.046 --> 28:52.921
to celebrate my nuptials.

28:53.005 --> 28:55.171
You will find, as you get older,

28:55.671 --> 28:57.796
that you begin to take stock of life.

28:59.338 --> 29:01.255
Not just where you've succeeded,

29:02.213 --> 29:03.505
but where you've failed.

29:05.255 --> 29:06.088
Who...

29:06.838 --> 29:07.838
you've failed.

29:15.213 --> 29:16.213
Suzi,

29:17.088 --> 29:18.380
my darling bride,

29:18.921 --> 29:21.963
who has so much of her life ahead of her.

29:23.796 --> 29:27.755
Grace, who shines so brightly
on the silver screen.

29:33.755 --> 29:36.005
Juan Carlos, my godson,

29:36.630 --> 29:39.963
who strives to lead my race team
to victory.

29:42.838 --> 29:43.838
You--

29:46.296 --> 29:47.255
Who are you?

29:48.713 --> 29:51.296
- Oh. Hey. We're the Spitzes.
- We're the--

29:51.671 --> 29:52.546
The who?

29:52.921 --> 29:55.463
Uh, I'm Audrey, and Nick Spitz.

29:55.838 --> 29:57.171
- Great.
- We love the boat.

29:57.255 --> 29:59.380
- A boat? I mean, this is a ship.
- It's beyond.

29:59.463 --> 30:01.755
- Never seen anything like this.
- Eric Lamonsoff has a boat.

30:01.838 --> 30:03.380
We go fishing. He's got a Boston Whaler.

30:03.463 --> 30:04.505
This is gigantic.

30:04.588 --> 30:06.296
They're my guests, Uncle.

30:06.588 --> 30:08.255
You brought guests?

30:08.338 --> 30:10.880
Well, you did take my plus-one.

30:11.588 --> 30:13.588
I'm so sorry. Would you like us to leave?

30:13.671 --> 30:16.046
We could-- I don't know
how we're getting out of here, though.

30:16.130 --> 30:18.921
We're-- We're out to sea.
Is there an Uber for boats?

30:19.005 --> 30:21.213
- Out-- Out of the room, Nick.
- Out of the room?

30:21.296 --> 30:22.838
We can go out of the room, absolutely--

30:22.921 --> 30:23.796
No.

30:24.380 --> 30:26.005
That won't be necessary.

30:26.338 --> 30:28.421
- Okay. So we'll stick around.
- So we stay. Okay.

30:29.213 --> 30:30.796
My nephew, Charles,

30:31.546 --> 30:33.963
who always finds a way
to keep me on my toes.

30:35.880 --> 30:39.796
My friend, the Colonel,
who's kept me safe these many years.

30:40.755 --> 30:45.963
Vikram, whose family fortunes have
always been intertwined with my own.

30:50.380 --> 30:51.963
And my Tobias.

30:52.921 --> 30:55.005
All I ever wanted was a son,

30:55.921 --> 30:57.213
and here you are.

30:58.005 --> 30:59.505
My boy.

31:03.463 --> 31:07.088
I've spoken to all of you
about your position in my will.

31:07.755 --> 31:12.005
I have thought long and hard
about what each of you is truly worth,

31:13.046 --> 31:15.171
and I've come to this conclusion.

31:16.380 --> 31:18.796
You are all leeches.

31:19.588 --> 31:20.671
Repugnant.

31:21.213 --> 31:22.255
Blood fat.

31:22.713 --> 31:27.255
Suckling on the tit of my good work
for so many years.

31:29.213 --> 31:30.546
You repulse me.

31:34.463 --> 31:36.546
Can't get this on a bus, baby.

31:36.630 --> 31:38.088
- This is incredible.
- I know it.

31:38.171 --> 31:39.296
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

31:39.380 --> 31:42.130
Which is why I have drafted a new will.

31:43.380 --> 31:46.005
It states that my entire fortune

31:46.671 --> 31:48.046
goes to Suzi.

31:51.838 --> 31:53.588
From this moment forth,

31:54.005 --> 31:55.463
you are all cut off.

31:56.505 --> 31:57.796
Abandoned.

31:57.880 --> 32:01.005
And perhaps,
after I've done you this kindness,

32:01.880 --> 32:05.130
you will finally be able to make
something of yourselves...

32:05.755 --> 32:06.880
on your own.

32:15.421 --> 32:18.421
Apparently, she's had enough of my caviar.

32:19.546 --> 32:21.130
- That was funny.
- Shh.

32:21.213 --> 32:22.296
Darling.

32:26.130 --> 32:27.755
You could've signed this at home.

32:28.255 --> 32:30.838
Instead, you called us here
to humiliate us?

32:30.921 --> 32:33.380
Yes, and you came running.

32:33.463 --> 32:34.671
Father, don't do this.

32:35.588 --> 32:36.796
Or what?

32:38.796 --> 32:39.838
Yes.

32:40.380 --> 32:41.755
That's what I thought.

32:55.963 --> 32:58.213
Don't shoot me!
Don't shoot me, please!

32:58.588 --> 33:00.046
Daddy!

33:13.630 --> 33:14.755
You shot him!

33:14.838 --> 33:16.005
No!

33:16.088 --> 33:17.546
I saw someone stab him.

33:17.630 --> 33:19.088
- Who?
- I don't know.

33:19.171 --> 33:20.380
What happened? I heard a scr--

33:21.671 --> 33:22.713
Malcolm!

33:22.796 --> 33:24.046
Oh, God!

33:24.671 --> 33:26.671
Has anybody tried to revive him?

33:26.755 --> 33:29.755
He's got a knife plunged in his heart.
I don't think he's revivable.

33:29.838 --> 33:30.838
Should we pull it out?

33:30.921 --> 33:33.171
No. It's a foot-long knife.
It's just like pulling--

33:36.963 --> 33:38.130
Oh, God!

33:38.213 --> 33:41.546
Wow! You should have left the knife in
for the po-po, Colonel, man!

33:41.630 --> 33:43.088
- I'll put it back.
- Don't put it back.

33:46.796 --> 33:49.130
Oh! Will you listen to my husband?
He's a detective.

33:49.213 --> 33:51.213
Yes, yes. What should we do, Mr. Officer?

33:51.296 --> 33:55.838
Well, for starters, let's stop removing
and reinserting the murder weapon

33:55.921 --> 33:57.380
into the victim's chest.

33:57.463 --> 34:00.005
In fact, let's stop
touching the body altogether.

34:00.088 --> 34:01.713
He was gonna take it all away.

34:03.005 --> 34:04.213
For you.

34:05.630 --> 34:06.463
Yo...

34:07.296 --> 34:08.380
Did he sign it?

34:13.045 --> 34:13.880
No.

34:13.963 --> 34:14.880
Yes!

34:14.963 --> 34:17.338
We should make sure
he doesn't have another copy on him.

34:17.630 --> 34:18.463
Uh-- Mm-mm.

34:18.545 --> 34:21.295
Rifling through the pockets of the corpse
counts as touching, yup.

34:21.380 --> 34:24.130
Sorry to single you out like that,
Ms. Ballard. You're wonderful.

34:24.213 --> 34:26.505
- You look extravagant tonight.
- Okay. What's next?

34:26.588 --> 34:28.545
We have to preserve the crime scene.

34:28.630 --> 34:31.338
Captain Wong, is there any way
you can lock off this place?

34:31.670 --> 34:32.588
Yes, of course.

34:32.670 --> 34:35.088
So we should then start
questioning the suspects.

34:35.380 --> 34:36.545
Suspects?

34:36.630 --> 34:38.213
We're not questioning anybody.

34:38.295 --> 34:40.920
Wong, when you finish locking up here,
you bring me the key.

34:41.005 --> 34:44.380
Then you radio Interpol, tell 'em
we'll meet 'em at the docks in Monaco.

34:44.463 --> 34:47.670
In the meantime, I'm gonna check
the shrimp out a little closer.

34:47.920 --> 34:49.213
For the investigation?

34:49.295 --> 34:51.463
No, Wong, because I'm hungry as shit.

34:51.545 --> 34:54.545
The rest of you, I'd lock yourselves
in your chambers or your yacht rooms

34:54.630 --> 34:55.920
because one of us...

34:57.171 --> 34:58.255
is a murderer.

35:03.796 --> 35:05.630
- Audrey.
- Yeah?

35:05.713 --> 35:07.088
Get the cocktail sauce.

35:07.713 --> 35:08.671
Yep.

35:31.963 --> 35:34.588
Wait a second. What on earth is on these?

35:34.671 --> 35:38.755
I don't know. This Maurice guy must
breastfeed each shrimp individually.

35:38.838 --> 35:40.380
I mean, they live so well.

35:40.463 --> 35:41.963
- Oh, God, yeah.
- God.

35:43.088 --> 35:44.963
All right. Where were we?
Okay, okay, okay.

35:45.546 --> 35:48.755
You know what? There had to be
two people in on the killing.

35:48.838 --> 35:51.338
Because how could they know
when the lights were gonna go out?

35:51.421 --> 35:53.255
- That's smart, that's smart.
- Right?

35:53.338 --> 35:55.505
I'm tired as hell right now.
I'm gonna go to sleep.

35:55.880 --> 35:56.880
- Are you kidding me?
- What?

35:57.296 --> 35:58.380
You're not jet-lagged?

36:02.338 --> 36:04.171
Nick.

36:04.255 --> 36:06.213
- Honey, come on, seriously.
- Huh?

36:06.296 --> 36:07.505
Who do you think did it?

36:08.546 --> 36:10.046
I don't think. I know.

36:10.796 --> 36:11.713
Who?

36:12.005 --> 36:13.255
It was the son.

36:13.755 --> 36:15.421
- Tobey.
- No.

36:15.505 --> 36:18.630
No way. Not a chance. It's too obvious.

36:18.713 --> 36:21.255
The most obvious suspect
is never, never the killer.

36:21.338 --> 36:24.671
The most obvious suspect
is always the killer.

36:24.755 --> 36:29.505
When a wife gets killed,
90% of the time it was the husband.

36:30.963 --> 36:32.755
Why did you just use that as an example?

36:33.755 --> 36:34.796
And I disagree.

36:34.880 --> 36:37.130
I think people are more complicated
than that.

36:39.171 --> 36:41.921
Judging off of what?
Those books that you read?

36:42.505 --> 36:44.921
People are simple, okay?

36:45.005 --> 36:45.963
It was Tobey.

36:46.046 --> 36:49.546
He had the most to gain,
and he also had the most to lose.

36:49.880 --> 36:52.296
Which is exactly why he's not the killer.

36:53.921 --> 36:55.921
Did you ever fool around on a boat?

36:56.463 --> 36:58.005
Do you know how much fun that could be?

36:58.088 --> 37:00.171
I just lay here
and the boat does all the work.

37:00.255 --> 37:02.546
- That's so convenient for you.
- You know I have a bad back.

37:02.630 --> 37:04.130
So convenient for you.

37:05.505 --> 37:07.046
What about the lights?

37:07.130 --> 37:10.213
Yeah, leave 'em on. I don't care.
Either way. Lady's choice.

37:10.296 --> 37:12.880
Shh! No. Who turned out those lights?

37:15.588 --> 37:17.296
What?! Oh!

37:28.046 --> 37:30.171
Don't look at me like that. I can feel it.

38:00.630 --> 38:02.546
- I'm sorry. Excuse me.
- Will you take the Allegra?

38:02.630 --> 38:03.796
It's the same stuff.

38:03.880 --> 38:05.755
- I don't want to talk about it.
- Oh, God.

38:09.046 --> 38:11.213
Enter the brilliant
yet tortured detective,

38:11.505 --> 38:12.505
right on cue.

38:13.255 --> 38:14.380
<i>Mesdames, messieurs.</i>

38:16.421 --> 38:19.130
My name is Inspector Laurent Delacroix.

38:20.963 --> 38:25.005
I will now summon you one by one
to the grand lounge for questioning.

38:31.171 --> 38:33.713
Why is that smoke ring so good?
How did he do that?

38:36.130 --> 38:38.171
Oh, you broke it. You broke it.

38:49.838 --> 38:51.421
Tell me about Malcolm Quince.

38:51.921 --> 38:54.296
He was the most wonderful--

38:54.380 --> 38:55.505
Swine.

38:55.588 --> 38:57.630
He was the love of my life.

38:57.713 --> 38:59.838
He was a complicated man.

39:01.130 --> 39:02.963
Describe to me what happened.

39:03.546 --> 39:08.338
Yo, Mr. French Policeman, man.
It was mad. Lights went out.

39:08.421 --> 39:10.880
I thought I saw something move,
and I shot.

39:13.713 --> 39:14.630
Yes.

39:14.713 --> 39:15.546
Finish line.

39:15.630 --> 39:17.713
The old man got what was coming to him.

39:17.796 --> 39:19.546
One-eight-seven, motherfu--

39:21.796 --> 39:23.588
Did anyone touch the body?

39:25.380 --> 39:26.463
No.

39:26.546 --> 39:30.255
And did you notice anything else
out of the ordinary?

39:31.130 --> 39:33.630
- The Americans.
- Yes, number one. Yes.

39:37.588 --> 39:39.296
Aren't you gonna, um...

39:39.380 --> 39:40.838
Aren't you gonna separate us?

39:42.838 --> 39:43.713
<i>Pardon?</i>

39:44.171 --> 39:45.880
- For the interrogation.
- Okay.

39:45.963 --> 39:47.588
Question us separately, see if our...

39:47.671 --> 39:49.505
- What are you doing?
- ...answers match.

39:49.588 --> 39:52.380
What? I'm just saying,
our answers will match

39:52.463 --> 39:54.296
- because we're innocent.
- Yeah, that's right.

39:55.796 --> 39:56.713
There we go.

39:56.796 --> 39:59.338
God, you are really good at that.

39:59.588 --> 40:02.963
We found this in Tobey Quince's suite.

40:03.630 --> 40:05.838
A typewritten suicide note

40:05.921 --> 40:08.671
in which he confesses
to the murder of his father.

40:09.255 --> 40:10.088
Typewritten?

40:10.171 --> 40:12.338
- Mm-mm.
- That's not very common.

40:12.796 --> 40:14.546
- Very suspicious.
- Yes.

40:14.630 --> 40:17.963
Yeah, obviously someone is trying
to frame Tobey for his father's murder.

40:18.963 --> 40:21.421
- This is amazing.
- Look how excited she is.

40:21.505 --> 40:23.296
So where's your head at
with this whole thing?

40:23.380 --> 40:24.963
I mean, who are your chief suspects?

40:26.338 --> 40:27.171
You.

40:27.255 --> 40:29.255
- Woo, yes.
- Right, of course,

40:29.338 --> 40:32.713
- 'cause everybody is a suspect.
- Especially her.

40:32.796 --> 40:36.255
This is a group of friends and family
who have known each other for years.

40:36.338 --> 40:39.338
You two show up, and ten hours later,
two of them are dead.

40:40.088 --> 40:40.963
Coincidence?

40:41.463 --> 40:43.046
- Yes.
- Absolutely.

40:43.130 --> 40:44.463
- Coincidence.
- Wait. Excuse me.

40:44.546 --> 40:46.046
Are you saying that your theory

40:46.130 --> 40:50.338
is that the two of us conned our way
onto a stranger's boat at the last minute

40:50.421 --> 40:54.421
to commit premeditated murder
that benefits us in no way?

40:54.505 --> 40:55.380
That's your theory?

40:55.880 --> 40:57.421
Perhaps someone paid you to do it.

40:57.505 --> 40:59.088
- No.
- Paid us to do it?

40:59.171 --> 41:01.963
Oh, my gosh. I would love to see that.
Show me that money.

41:02.046 --> 41:04.005
Do you want to see
our bank statements?

41:04.380 --> 41:06.338
We're broke.

41:06.421 --> 41:08.380
Desperate for money. I see.

41:08.463 --> 41:10.421
Now you gave him a motive.

41:10.505 --> 41:12.671
- No, no, no. I know. Just don't...
- We did this because--

41:12.755 --> 41:14.671
- ...take my words out of context.
- We got nothing.

41:14.755 --> 41:16.171
- That's all we got, is nothing.
- No.

41:16.255 --> 41:19.546
Listen, I am talking to you,
detective to detective.

41:20.088 --> 41:21.046
We didn't do this.

41:21.130 --> 41:23.588
- You can see in my eyes. You can tell.
- Mm-mm.

41:24.088 --> 41:27.338
Perhaps I will have
that word with you independently.

41:28.130 --> 41:29.296
I di-- Hey!

41:30.630 --> 41:31.546
I can get up.

41:31.630 --> 41:32.963
Hey, okay.

41:33.046 --> 41:34.463
I'll be out in a minute.

41:34.963 --> 41:36.046
I love you.

41:36.130 --> 41:38.713
I'm sorry. She's just excited
because it's--

41:38.796 --> 41:41.213
She reads books, and this is fun for her.

41:43.546 --> 41:46.171
You wish me to believe you're innocent.

41:46.255 --> 41:48.671
Unfortunately, I do not believe liars.

41:48.755 --> 41:50.255
But I'm telling you the truth.

41:50.338 --> 41:52.796
And how long
have you been lying to your wife?

41:52.880 --> 41:53.713
Excuse me?

41:54.630 --> 41:57.630
You did not think that we would
investigate your background,

41:58.088 --> 42:01.546
Sergeant Nicholas Spitz, NYPD?

42:02.005 --> 42:05.380
Failed his detective's exam three times.

42:05.463 --> 42:07.588
You are, how you do say,

42:07.671 --> 42:08.921
cop on the beat,

42:09.005 --> 42:11.088
not detective as you so claim.

42:11.838 --> 42:12.838
So I...

42:13.838 --> 42:15.421
tell people I'm a detective.

42:15.505 --> 42:16.713
There's--

42:16.796 --> 42:18.005
That's not a crime.

42:18.380 --> 42:21.213
Impersonating a detective <i>is </i> a crime.

42:21.630 --> 42:23.005
I didn't think it was a crime here.

42:23.088 --> 42:24.796
I thought maybe you guys
had different rules.

42:25.296 --> 42:27.005
That doesn't make us murderers.

42:27.088 --> 42:30.671
A broke, failed man, lying to his wife?
I think it does.

42:30.963 --> 42:33.463
You don't have any evidence.
You can't hold us.

42:33.546 --> 42:35.880
No, but I can hold these.

42:37.088 --> 42:40.588
I believe Mr. Cavendish has provided
accommodations for you

42:40.671 --> 42:43.755
at the Hotel de Savoie,
so you won't be on the street.

42:44.421 --> 42:47.380
But mark my words, Officer Spitz,

42:47.880 --> 42:51.671
I will not rest until I prove
that you committed these murders.

42:52.296 --> 42:53.255
And I...

42:54.088 --> 42:57.463
will rest, because I'm tired as shit,
at that hotel you just said.

42:57.546 --> 42:59.046
It sounds like a good one.

42:59.130 --> 43:01.713
But after I'm well-rested
and I eat breakfast--

43:01.796 --> 43:04.421
hopefully the guy cooks
as good as Maurice--

43:05.255 --> 43:07.796
I will not rest until I prove to you

43:07.880 --> 43:10.171
we have nothing to do with these murders.

43:15.005 --> 43:15.838
Juan Carlos!

43:15.921 --> 43:17.130
Juan Carlos!

43:20.671 --> 43:23.005
Charles said
that everyone's gonna be at this race,

43:23.088 --> 43:24.921
so whoever did this is gonna be there.

43:25.005 --> 43:26.296
We have to figure out who it is.

43:26.380 --> 43:29.505
I know we've gotta figure it out.
This isn't one of your books, sweetheart.

43:29.588 --> 43:32.046
I mean, it's like one of your books,
but this is real.

43:32.130 --> 43:34.255
Like, two people are dead, for real.

43:34.338 --> 43:36.255
- I know.
- There's a real killer on the real loose.

43:36.338 --> 43:37.505
Hey, babe. Relax.

43:37.588 --> 43:39.171
What's-- What's wrong with you?

43:39.255 --> 43:41.921
For real? Come on. Will you just focus...

43:42.005 --> 43:43.005
- Fine.
- ...on this with me?

43:43.088 --> 43:44.671
Um, yes. Uh...

43:44.755 --> 43:47.671
Okay. So there are three basic
motives for every murder.

43:47.755 --> 43:49.671
Yes. The first one is money.

43:49.755 --> 43:50.630
Right.

43:50.713 --> 43:52.671
Everyone was in Quince's will,
except Suzi.

43:52.755 --> 43:54.713
- Okay.
- All right. The second one is love.

43:54.796 --> 43:57.130
We know nobody loved that guy
'cause he was kind of a prick.

43:57.213 --> 43:58.296
Suzi might have loved him.

43:58.380 --> 44:00.630
- That's what you would think--
- Okay, what's the third one?

44:00.713 --> 44:01.880
- Revenge.
- Right.

44:01.963 --> 44:03.588
That's the one
we should be thinking about.

44:03.671 --> 44:06.046
I'm telling you, if we figure out
who hates this guy the most,

44:06.130 --> 44:07.005
that's our killer.

44:07.088 --> 44:08.421
Okay. Okay.

44:18.088 --> 44:20.796
So, this beard... It's incredible.

44:20.880 --> 44:23.671
Do you oil that or condition?

44:23.755 --> 44:25.255
You won't get anything out of him.

44:25.338 --> 44:26.671
Oh, my gosh.

44:26.755 --> 44:29.796
Most of his life, he's been serving men
like me and Malcolm,

44:30.130 --> 44:32.005
despite being an heir to millions.

44:32.088 --> 44:33.296
He's rich, too?

44:33.380 --> 44:35.713
He's supposed to be,
but he's one of 16 children,

44:35.796 --> 44:37.713
and he's half French.

44:37.796 --> 44:40.255
Are you familiar
with French inheritance law?

44:40.630 --> 44:41.588
Broad strokes.

44:41.671 --> 44:44.130
That Colonel guy,
he's getting on my nerves.

